---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import attackJan30 from '../assets/attack-text-jan30.jpg';
import attackFeb24 from '../assets/attack-text-feb24.jpg';

const mailtoHref =
  'mailto:hello@alexbores.io?subject=I%20want%20to%20help%20elect%20Alex%20Bores' +
  '&body=Name%3A%0A%0A' +
  'Where%20I%20live%20(NY-12%20%2F%20NYC%20%2F%20elsewhere%20in%20NY%20%2F%20out%20of%20state)%3A%0A%0A' +
  'Time%20I%20can%20spend%20(a%20couple%20hours%20%2F%205%E2%80%9320%20hours%20%2F%20more)%3A%0A%0A' +
  'What%20I%27m%20up%20for%20(pick%20any%3A%20messaging%20friends%20%2F%20canvassing%20%2F%20phone%20or%20text%20banking%20%2F%20donating%20%2F%20skills%20%2F%20other)%3A%0A%0A' +
  'Anything%20else%20we%20should%20know%3A%0A';
---
<Base title="Got friends in NY-12? Help elect Alex Bores. · alexbores.io">

  <aside class="sidebar-toc" aria-label="Section navigation">
    <p class="sidebar-prompt">sections</p>
    <ol class="sidebar-list">
      <li>
        <a href="#alex" data-section="alex">
          <span class="s-tree">├──</span>
          <span class="s-num">01</span>
          <span class="s-file">why-alex.md</span>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#strategy" data-section="strategy">
          <span class="s-tree">├──</span>
          <span class="s-num">02</span>
          <span class="s-file">our-strategy.md</span>
        </a>
        <ol class="sidebar-sublist">
          <li>
            <a href="#district" data-section="district">
              <span class="s-tree">│   ├──</span>
              <span class="s-file">the-district.md</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#dates" data-section="dates">
              <span class="s-tree">│   └──</span>
              <span class="s-file">key-dates.md</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#volunteer" data-section="volunteer">
          <span class="s-tree">└──</span>
          <span class="s-num">03</span>
          <span class="s-file">where-we-need-you.md</span>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </aside>

  <p class="eyebrow">alexbores.io</p>

  <h1 class="hero">
    Got friends in NY-12? Help elect <span class="accent">Alex Bores</span>.
  </h1>

  <p class="lede">
    A volunteer-run relational organizing effort, aimed at people in tech, EA, and adjacent communities.
  </p>

  <nav class="toc" aria-label="Page sections">
    <p class="toc-prompt">sections</p>
    <ol class="toc-list">
      <li>
        <a href="#alex">
          <span class="toc-tree">├──</span>
          <span class="toc-num">01</span>
          <span class="toc-file">why-alex.md</span>
          <span class="toc-desc">Why OpenAI is spending millions to beat him.</span>
        </a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#strategy">
          <span class="toc-tree">├──</span>
          <span class="toc-num">02</span>
          <span class="toc-file">our-strategy.md</span>
          <span class="toc-desc">The math, and the plan.</span>
        </a>
        <ol class="toc-sublist">
          <li>
            <a href="#district">
              <span class="toc-tree">│   ├──</span>
              <span class="toc-file">the-district.md</span>
              <span class="toc-desc">Who lives in NY-12.</span>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="#dates">
              <span class="toc-tree">│   └──</span>
              <span class="toc-file">key-dates.md</span>
              <span class="toc-desc">June 13, June 23.</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#volunteer">
          <span class="toc-tree">└──</span>
          <span class="toc-num">03</span>
          <span class="toc-file">where-we-need-you.md</span>
          <span class="toc-desc">Ways to help — and how to sign up.</span>
        </a>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- WHY ALEX (includes voices) -->
  <section class="block" id="alex">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">why alex?</p>
    <h2>OpenAI's <em>$10 million</em><sup class="cite"><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/03/ai-companies-are-spending-millions-to-thwart-this-former-tech-execs-congressional-bid/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[1]</a></sup> campaign against Alex.</h2>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
      <p>NY-12 primary voters are blanketed with texts of the like:</p>
    </div>
    <div class="attack-grid">
      <figure class="attack-figure">
        <Image src={attackJan30} alt="SMS screenshot attacking Bores for his work at Palantir, the company that powers ICE. Paid for by Think Big PAC." class="attack-screenshot" loading="lazy" widths={[400, 600, 800]} sizes="(min-width: 640px) 380px, 100vw" />
        <figcaption class="attack-caption">Jan 30, 2026 · Think Big PAC</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="attack-figure">
        <Image src={attackFeb24} alt="SMS screenshot citing alleged Bloomberg reporting on Bores' time at Palantir. Paid for by Think Big PAC." class="attack-screenshot" loading="lazy" widths={[400, 600, 800]} sizes="(min-width: 640px) 380px, 100vw" />
        <figcaption class="attack-caption">Feb 24, 2026 · Think Big PAC</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <p class="see-also">
      See also <a href="/voices">voices.md</a> — press coverage and on-record commentary from Eric Neyman, Scott Alexander, Ezra Klein, and more.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR STRATEGY -->
  <section class="block" id="strategy">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">our strategy</p>
    <h2>Our strategy: win knowledge workers.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The NY-12 Democratic primary is on <strong>June 23, 2026</strong>. Primaries like this are typically decided by a few hundred to a few thousand votes — turnout is low, persuasion is tractable, and most people haven't thought about it yet.</p>
      <p>Collectively, our communities know <em>thousands</em> of registered Democrats in NY-12. If a few hundred of us each have a real conversation with 3–5 friends, we can plausibly move a hundred-plus votes. In a race this size, that's material.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 id="district">The district</h3>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-bottom: 14px;">
      <p>NY-12 is among the most educated, highest-income districts in the country. If you're in tech, EA, or adjacent circles, your network disproportionately overlaps with it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="data-table-wrap">
      <table class="data-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Metric</th>
            <th scope="col">NY-12</th>
            <th scope="col">NYC overall</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Bachelor's degree or higher (25+)</th>
            <td>81%</td>
            <td>42.5%</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Median household income</th>
            <td>$153,117</td>
            <td>$81,228</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Per capita income</th>
            <td>$138,927</td>
            <td>$52,504</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Population</th>
            <td>752,016</td>
            <td>~8.3M</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Poverty rate</th>
            <td>8.2%</td>
            <td>~18%</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="data-caption">Source: Census Reporter, NY-12 profile<sup class="cite"><a href="https://censusreporter.org/profiles/50000US3612-congressional-district-12-ny/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[2]</a></sup></p>

    <h3 id="dates">Key dates</h3>
    <div class="dates">
      <div class="date-cell">
        <p class="date-label">Jun 13 · Saturday</p>
        <p class="date-value">Registration deadline</p>
        <p class="date-desc">Last day to register. Early voting <em>also</em> begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="date-cell">
        <p class="date-label">Jun 23 · Tuesday</p>
        <p class="date-value">Election day</p>
        <p class="date-desc">Polls open. Primary <em>election day</em>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top: 20px;">
      <p>If you want to contact someone who isn't registered to vote in New York, they need to register by <strong>June 13</strong>. It's too late to re-register with a party affiliation, so outreach should focus on current registered Democrats and unregistered New Yorkers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHERE WE NEED YOU -->
  <section class="block" id="volunteer">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">where we need you</p>
    <h2>Where we need you</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <a class="card" href="#relational">
        <p class="card-eyebrow">Relational</p>
        <h4>Message 3–5 friends in NY-12</h4>
        <p>~2–5 hrs over six weeks. The thing we most need volunteers for.</p>
        <span class="card-more">How it works →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="#other-local">
        <p class="card-eyebrow">Hands-on</p>
        <h4>Canvass, phones, or poll greet</h4>
        <p>Best if you're in NY-12 or NYC. Remote phone/text banking works from anywhere.</p>
        <span class="card-more">See options →</span>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="#other-anywhere">
        <p class="card-eyebrow">Support</p>
        <h4>Donate, lend skills, or amplify</h4>
        <p>FEC limits apply. Pro skills need to be at market rate unless genuinely volunteer.</p>
        <span class="card-more">See details →</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <h3 id="relational">The main ask: relational organizing</h3>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Roughly two to five hours of your time across six weeks, doing the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Find 3–5 people you know in NY-12.</strong> We'll show you <a href="https://reach.vote/">Reach</a>, an app that cross-references your contacts against the voter file.</li>
        <li><strong>Message them.</strong> Text, call, whatever's natural. Tell them why you care about Bores.</li>
        <li><strong>Ask if they'll vote.</strong> Help them make a concrete plan — "I'll early-vote Saturday morning" beats "yeah, probably."</li>
        <li><strong>Follow up.</strong> Once closer to election day, a short check-in.</li>
        <li><strong>Log it</strong> so we can tell who's already been contacted — the goal is one friend reaching out, not ten.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You don't have to do anything aversive. If you want to do more, we'll find things.</p>

      <h4>Who should reach out to friends?</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>People in New York City</strong> — more latitude, it's not weird to organize politically in your own city.</li>
        <li><strong>People outside New York</strong> — only for contacts you'd already text casually. Don't cold-message someone you haven't spoken to in five years; that reads as weird and is counterproductive.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 id="other">Other ways to help</h3>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Relational outreach isn't for everyone, and not everyone knows people in NY-12. Plenty of other useful things:</p>

      <h4 id="other-local">If you're in NY-12 or NYC</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Canvassing with the campaign</li>
        <li>Phone or text banking off campaign-provided lists</li>
        <li>Poll greeting on election day (Jun 23) or during early voting (Jun 13–22)</li>
        <li>Showing up at events — visibility helps</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 id="other-anywhere">If you're anywhere</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Donating</strong> to the campaign (FEC limits apply)</li>
        <li><strong>Remote phone or text banking</strong> — works from anywhere</li>
        <li><strong>Skills</strong> — design, dev, writing, ops. If you do this professionally and want to contribute, read the FEC note below first</li>
        <li><strong>Thoughtful amplification</strong> online — substantive posts from people who know the candidate beat generic "vote for X" spam</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 id="join">Get involved</h3>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
      <p>Tell us a little about you and we'll match you to something useful — probably within a day or two. Relational outreach, something else, we'll figure it out.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-block">
      <a class="btn" href={mailtoHref}>
        Count me in →
      </a>
      <p class="cta-help">Opens an email with a short template. Or just write a sentence — we'll take it from there. Either way, <a href="mailto:hello@alexbores.io">hello@alexbores.io</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="block" id="faq">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">faq</p>
    <h2>Concerns, addressed</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Is this legal / okay with campaign finance rules?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>Volunteer time is fine. Spending money on this effort (merch, paid ads, etc.) can count as an in-kind contribution and needs to be reported — talk to us before spending. Professional services (design, engineering, etc.) done for the campaign need to be at market rate unless you do it as a genuine volunteer for something unrelated to your profession. None of this is legal advice; if you have a specific question, ask a lawyer.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What's the campaign's involvement?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>The campaign provides guidance on messaging and best practices. They don't manage this effort, and we don't speak for them.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I talk to the media about this?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>Please don't, by default. If you're getting press questions, forward them to us and we'll connect you to someone appropriate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What if Bores loses?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>He might — this is a competitive primary. We're being upfront about that. The case for trying is that a few hours of your time has a real probability of moving the outcome, and either way you'll have had honest conversations with people you care about.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do you keep contacts from being messaged by ten different people?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>There's a shared tracker of who's reached out to whom. When you sign up, you get assigned specific contacts and we coordinate to avoid the pile-on problem.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What if I don't want to message friends?</summary>
        <div class="answer">
          <p>Totally fine — plenty of other ways to help, see the list above. Mention it in the email and we'll skip straight to something else.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<script>
  const links = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLAnchorElement>('.sidebar-list a[data-section]');
  const linkById = new Map<string, HTMLAnchorElement>();
  links.forEach((l) => {
    const id = l.dataset.section;
    if (id) linkById.set(id, l);
  });

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      for (const entry of entries) {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          links.forEach((l) => l.classList.remove('active'));
          const link = linkById.get(entry.target.id);
          if (link) link.classList.add('active');
        }
      }
    },
    { rootMargin: '-45% 0px -45% 0px', threshold: 0 }
  );

  ['alex', 'strategy', 'district', 'dates', 'volunteer'].forEach((id) => {
    const el = document.getElementById(id);
    if (el) observer.observe(el);
  });
</script>
